{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b7109db7-d9af-4234-aae5-06a3cff28005","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **4.6.0+** (you already have this ✅).\n\n2. **Remove** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference.\n\n3. **Add** the `NUnit.Runner.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform` package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Runner.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform\" Version=\"0.2.0-alpha.2\" />\n   ```\n\n4. **Enable the new platform** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Set output type** to `Exe` (the test project becomes a self-contained executable):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nAfter these changes, `dotnet test` will use Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest. You can also run the test assembly directly as an executable.\n\n> **Note:** The NUnit runner extension is still in **pre-release**. Check [NuGet](https://www.nuget.org/packages/NUnit.Runner.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform) for the latest version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7b1c121a-55d9-45fd-a3a2-f282c1a2045a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":413,"requestId":"7C1F:DF52E:272DD77:2B31F00:69F93E91"},"id":"c13a5d79-456a-4f6d-8d82-636ca595105e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:30.651Z","parentId":"aeda0a6e-5a56-4bb8-bb71-2e2365cec801"}
